<item>
            <title>[FUNCTOR-23] aggregator.xml generates broken JavaDoc links</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FUNCTOR-23</link>
                <project id="12312520" key="FUNCTOR">Commons Functor (Dormant)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;aggregator.xml&lt;/tt&gt; has a few JavaDoc links to methods, as such the anchor url contains a hash (#) as well as a method name followed by brackets (). This triggers Doxia/Velocity into &quot;thinking&quot; that this is a macro call, and as such the links resulted (during &lt;tt&gt;mvn site&lt;/tt&gt;) do not contain these brackets.&lt;br/&gt;
To fix them, as per &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MSITE-646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MSITE-646&lt;/a&gt;, we need to URL-escape the # hash sign (%23).&lt;br/&gt;
This bug is created to propose a patch to &lt;tt&gt;aggregator.xml&lt;/tt&gt; for this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12600379">FUNCTOR-23</key>
